{{!
    @template mod_streak/avatar

    A learner avatar: their uploaded photo when present, otherwise a deterministic colored initials
    disc so the row still reads as an individual. Rendered from data only, so a theme can fully
    restyle it (override this template or the .mod-streak-avatar* CSS).

    Context variables required for this template:
    * haspicture bool Whether the user has an uploaded picture
    * pictureurl string The picture URL (when haspicture)
    * initials string Up to two initials (when not haspicture)
    * colorindex int Palette index 0-7 (when not haspicture)
    * large bool Render the larger headline variant

    Example context (json):
    {
        "haspicture": false,
        "pictureurl": "",
        "initials": "AG",
        "colorindex": 2,
        "large": true
    }
}}
{{#haspicture}}
    <img class="mod-streak-avatar{{#large}} mod-streak-avatar-lg{{/large}}" src="{{pictureurl}}" alt="">
{{/haspicture}}
{{^haspicture}}
    <span class="mod-streak-avatar mod-streak-initials mod-streak-avatar-c{{colorindex}}{{#large}} mod-streak-avatar-lg{{/large}}" aria-hidden="true">{{initials}}</span>
{{/haspicture}}
